def: Never again; at no time hereafter. Testament of Love. Tyndale.Where springtime of the Hesperides Begins, but endeth nevermore.Longfellow.
To become channeled, as a candle when the flame flares in thewind.
Capable of being uttered or explained; utterable. Barrow.
A buttress of an arch; the supporter, or that part which joinsit to the upright pier.
Having wheels of the same size or diameter; having equalrotation. [R.]
Having mild and salubrious qualities. [Obs.] Bacon.
Disposed to embrace; fond of caressing. [R.] Thackeray.
